WLMS does not expose CreateWlsDomain in
v65.110.0, so the published runtime is
bind/manage-existing only. Untracked reconciles
must resolve an existing domain by explicit
spec.id or by an exact unique list match before
any update or delete can proceed.
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE as
success, DELETING as terminating, and FAILED or
NEEDS_ATTENTION as terminal failure.
UpdateWlsDomain only reconciles configuration
and tag fields. ChangeWlsDomainCompartment
remains out of scope, so compartmentId,
displayName, middlewareType, and weblogicVersion
stay bind-only replacement drift.
DeleteWlsDomain returns no work-request
identifier. The runtime relies on GetWlsDomain
or ListWlsDomains rereads to confirm DELETED or
NOT_FOUND before finalizer release.
end note
